        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:51PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Yuma, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Yuma around 500 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Goodland.</instruction>
